      "title": "Sherpa left for dead on Everest tells his story",
      "content_html": "<a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/07/13/sherpa-left-for-dead-on-everest-tells-his-story.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Sherpa left for dead on Everest tells his story\"><img alt=\"Mount Everest (Julia Mountain Photo/shutterstock.com)\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"512\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/everest-e1782835729237.jpg?fit=768%2C512&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"768\" /></a><p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">\"Hillary\" Dawa Sherpa was presumed dead on Everest. His family had begun funeral rites. Then a cleanup crew found him crawling near the Khumbu Icefall.</p>\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Everest stories either arrive dressed up as triumph: flags, summits, sponsor logos, oxygen bottles, a human doing something expensive and stupid at altitude, or a person turned into a popsicle. &#8212; <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/07/13/sherpa-left-for-dead-on-everest-tells-his-story.html\">Read the rest </a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/07/13/sherpa-left-for-dead-on-everest-tells-his-story.html\">Sherpa left for dead on Everest tells his story</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://boingboing.net\">Boing Boing</a>.</p>",
